Real Madrid have published their starting XI for the Champions League final on Saturday evening. The LaLiga have made the bold move of announcing their squad for the match with less than three hours left to kick off. Karim Benzema captains the side and is supported by Vinicius Jr in the attack. Thibaut Courtois starts in goal and the back four in front of him are: Dani Carvajal, Eder Militao, David Alaba and Ferland Mendy. Luka Modric, Casemiro and Toni Kroos start in midfield. Real Madrid starting XI vs Liverpool: Courtois, Carvajal, Militao, Alaba, Kroos, Benzema, Modric, Casemiro, Valverde, Vinicius Jr, Mendy